Language name: NONI
Language number: 4139
Alternate names: 
Classification: Niger-Kordofanian, Bantoid
Comments: Noni has 3 level tones.  All two-tone sequences 
apart from MH also occur on monosyllables. Short /U/ 
conditions a labio-dental fricative offglide from a 
preceding stop.
Sources: 

Hyman, L.M. 1981. Noni Grammatical Structure, with special 
rreference to verb morphology. Southern California 
Occasional Papers in Linguistics no.9